Traditional AI vs Generative AI vs Generative AI + RAG
-------------------------------------------------------

| No.    | Traditional AI                                                                   | Generative AI                                              | Generative AI + RAG                                                                |
| ------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **1**  | Main Purpose: Predicts a class, value, or decision                               | Generates new content (text, code, images, etc.)           | Generates answers using retrieved external knowledge                               |
| **2**  | Input: Structured/labeled data                                                   | Prompt or instruction                                      | Prompt + External documents (PDFs, databases, websites)                            |
| **3**  | Training: Requires training on a specific dataset                                | Uses a pre-trained Large Language Model (LLM)              | Uses a pre-trained LLM + Retrieval system (no model retraining)                    |
| **4**  | Knowledge Source: Training dataset only                                          | Knowledge learned during pre-training                      | Latest documents retrieved at query time                                           |
| **5**  | Output: Classification, regression, prediction                                   | Human-like generated content                               | Accurate, context-aware generated content                                          |
| **6**  | Data Updates: Retrain the model when data changes                                | Cannot automatically learn new private data                | Simply update documents or vector database; no retraining required                 |
| **7**  | Hallucination Risk: Low for trained tasks                                        | Higher because the model may guess                         | Lower because answers are grounded in retrieved information                        |
| **8**  | Common Technologies: Decision Tree, SVM, Random Forest, XGBoost, Neural Networks | GPT, Gemini, Claude, Llama, Mistral                        | GPT/Gemini/Claude + FAISS, ChromaDB, Pinecone, LangChain, LlamaIndex               |
| **9**  | Real-Time Example: Spam detection, fraud detection, house price prediction       | Email writing, code generation, story writing, translation | HR chatbot, document Q&A, legal assistant, medical chatbot, product catalog search |
| **10** | Best Use Cases: Fixed prediction tasks with labeled data                         | Creative and conversational AI                             | Enterprise AI with company-specific and up-to-date information                     |


