One-line definitions
Traditional AI: Learns from labeled data to make predictions or classifications.
Generative AI: Uses a pre-trained LLM to generate new content from prompts.
Generative AI + RAG: Retrieves relevant external information first, then uses an LLM to generate accurate, up-to-date answers.

